🎯 Summary

Cloud Computing allows organizations to deploy applications without managing physical infrastructure.

Public cloud providers like AWS manage hardware, networking, storage, and security, enabling customers to focus on application development.

AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) is one of the most important AWS services. It helps securely manage users, permissions, groups, and roles by ensuring that users receive only the access they need.

Understanding these core concepts provides a strong foundation for learning advanced AWS services such as EC2, S3, VPC, RDS, Lambda, and more.

